12. Second Question. An unjust Law, it appears, ought not to be made3 but being made, does it bind the conscience? Is it among the things of which we say, It ought not to have been done: being done, it is valid?

For it may be that what cannot be commanded without sin, may be performed without sin. True obedience is not disputatious.

But we have already shewn (Proeleot. v. Art. 7), that unjust Laws do not bind the conscience.
